# Web UI Conventions

## File Structure

```
wwwroot/
├── index.html          # Dashboard page
├── log-search.html     # Search page
├── advanced-search.html # Query builder
├── css/
│   └── dashboard.css   # All styles, theme variables
└── js/
    ├── api.js          # Shared fetch wrapper
    ├── dashboard.js    # Dashboard logic
    ├── log-search.js   # Search page logic
    └── components/
        └── logs-renderer.js  # Reusable log table renderer
```

## API Calls

Always use `api.js` wrapper (handles DedgeAuth token auth):

```javascript
// GET
const response = await Api.get('/api/Dashboard/summary');

// POST
const response = await Api.post('/api/Logs/search', { PageSize: 50 });

// Access data (PascalCase!)
if (response.Success) {
    const logs = response.Data.Items;
    console.log(logs[0].ComputerName);  // PascalCase
}
```

## LogsRenderer Component

Reusable log table with expandable rows, modals, copy buttons:

```javascript
const renderer = new LogsRenderer({
    maxEntries: 50,
    showCopyButtons: true,
    showExpandable: true,
    onOpenModal: (log) => openLogDetailModal(log)
});
renderer.render(document.getElementById('logsBody'), logs);
```

## Theme Support

CSS variables in `dashboard.css`:
- `--bg-primary`, `--bg-card`, `--text-primary`
- Toggle via `data-theme="dark"` on `<html>`

## Toast Notifications

```javascript
function showToast(message) {
    const toast = document.createElement('div');
    toast.className = 'toast-notification show';
    toast.textContent = message;
    document.body.appendChild(toast);
    setTimeout(() => toast.remove(), 2000);
}
```
